Package communication.messages.objects

Class InGameCharacter

  • java.lang.Object
    • communication.messages.objects.Entities
      • communication.messages.objects.InGameCharacter
  • public class InGameCharacter
extends Entities
    Message-Class, which is responsible to describe the Entity Character which can be placed on the map Characters are needed e.g. for GameStateEvents
    Author:
    Sarah Engele

    • Constructor Detail

      • InGameCharacter

        public InGameCharacter​(java.lang.String name,
                       int PID,
                       int ID,
                       int HP,
                       int MP,
                       int AP,
                       int[] stones,
                       int[] position)
        the constructor of the Character-Class. Creates a Character-MessageObject.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the Character (e.g. Wonder Woman)
        PID - might be the Player ID (Player1 or Player2) that the Character belongs to
        ID - the ID of this specific Character (every Character has an ID, see also in IDs class)
        HP - the amount of Health Points (HP) the Character currently has
        MP - the amount of Movement Points (MP) the Character currently has
        AP - the amount of Action Points (AP) the Character currently has
        stones - the inventory of the Character that might contain Infinity Stones
        position - the position where the character is placed on the map
